01:45.186 --> 01:47.085
Nice pumpkin.

01:48.222 --> 01:49.888
Thank you.

01:49.890 --> 01:53.525
Probably won't be any kids
coming this far out, but...

01:53.527 --> 01:56.395
it's tradition, right?

01:56.397 --> 01:58.997
Yeah.

01:58.999 --> 02:01.033
Yeah, you know,
Danny's daughter dropped one

02:01.035 --> 02:02.901
at my place yesterday.

02:05.239 --> 02:07.506
Ready to go?

02:08.642 --> 02:10.542
It's gonna be a
walk in the park.

02:10.544 --> 02:13.779
You got nothing
to worry about, okay?

02:25.392 --> 02:27.192
Remember, um...

02:27.194 --> 02:31.396
in my statement to the HPD,
I said that Gray

02:31.398 --> 02:33.699
came at me with a knife?

02:35.436 --> 02:37.202
That's not what happened.

02:37.204 --> 02:39.838
I need you to send officers
to my home right away.

02:39.840 --> 02:41.974
You're gonna put me in jail?
Come now, Alicia.

02:41.976 --> 02:44.276
Do you really think
that's gonna put an end to it?

02:44.278 --> 02:45.944
Ma'am, hello?

02:45.946 --> 02:48.981
There's only one way
to put an end to this.

02:48.983 --> 02:50.782
What's the nature
of your emergency?

02:50.784 --> 02:53.518
I need to report a murder.

02:53.520 --> 02:57.489
I could have held my gun on Gray
until HPD got there.

02:57.491 --> 03:00.392
I knew...

03:00.394 --> 03:02.995
that she was never
gonna let me go

03:02.997 --> 03:05.697
unless I put
a stop to it.

03:05.699 --> 03:07.733
Okay, um...

03:07.735 --> 03:09.635
first of all,
I didn't hear any of that.

03:09.637 --> 03:11.870
Okay? Second of all, Alicia,
you can never

03:11.872 --> 03:13.805
tell anybody
what you just told me.

03:13.807 --> 03:15.540
Do you understand?
You can't tell your lawyer.

03:15.542 --> 03:17.442
Not your daughter.
Nobody ever.

03:17.444 --> 03:19.311
Well, maybe they'll think of it
as self-defense

03:19.313 --> 03:21.313
and they'll let me go.

03:21.315 --> 03:23.248
Are you willing
to take that chance?

03:23.250 --> 03:25.684
I can't take the stand
and commit perjury.

03:26.820 --> 03:28.754
Then you don't take the stand.

03:28.756 --> 03:30.088
Okay? You don't testify.

03:30.090 --> 03:31.456
When a defendant

03:31.458 --> 03:33.792
in a murder trial
doesn't take the stand,

03:33.794 --> 03:35.060
it's basically
an admission of guilt.

03:35.062 --> 03:36.528
I just have
to tell the truth.

03:36.530 --> 03:37.929
If I don't,

03:37.931 --> 03:40.465
I'm just as bad
as the people I put away.

03:40.467 --> 03:41.733
Well, you know what?
You're wrong.

03:41.735 --> 03:43.268
That woman was a
serial killer.

03:43.270 --> 03:44.436
She deserved to die.

03:44.438 --> 03:45.771
And let me tell you
something else.

03:45.773 --> 03:46.772
The young lady in that house...

03:46.774 --> 03:47.906
Alicia, that young lady
in there,

03:47.908 --> 03:49.541
she lost her mother
for five years.

03:49.543 --> 03:50.942
She does not deserve

03:50.944 --> 03:52.077
to lose you again.

03:52.079 --> 03:53.512
Have you thought about that?

03:54.682 --> 03:56.648
I'm gonna put my faith
in the system.

03:56.650 --> 03:58.517
It was self-defense.

03:58.519 --> 03:59.851
What if that jury doesn't see it

03:59.853 --> 04:01.620
the way you see it?

04:04.458 --> 04:10.228
Then I... then I need to ask you
to take care of her.

